name: rsass
description: Sass reimplemented in rust with nom (early stage)
contribution_justification: Projects on GitHub by default use issues and pull requests, as encouraged by documentation such as <https://guides.github.com/activities/contributing-to-open-source/>.
contribution_requirements_justification: https://github.com/kaj/rsass - Last section specifies that the code is checked with rustfmt (the config is very close to rustfmt default and include in the repository in the way that makes rustfmt find it by default.
license_location_justification: Non-trivial license location file in repository: <https://github.com/kaj/rsass/blob/master/LICENSE>.
floss_license_osi_justification: Both Apache-2.0 and MIT are OSI-approved
documentation_basics_justification: https://docs.rs/rsass
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: Releases are handled by cargo and uses semantic versioning.
release_notes_vulns_justification: No known vulnerabilities (there has been (and may still be) crash bugs which might be considered denial of service vulnerabilities.  Those are mentioned in release notes when fixed, but does not have CVE assigned.
report_responses_justification: Response time varies, but has not been worse than a month yet.
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: Github issues, but not yet properly documented.  Only public reports at the moment.
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: There has been no actual vulnerability reports. Crash bugs has been acknowledged within 14 days.
build_common_tools_justification: The project is mainly a rust library.  Cargo is the default build system and dependency manager for rust.
test_justification: Cargo test runs the test suites.  There is also a program (in the repository) for generating a local test suite from the official sass specification test suite.
test_policy_justification: New functionality is mainly developed against the sass specification test suite, and the local test suite is updated as functionality is progressing.
tests_documented_added_justification: It's not ok, it's just not properly done yet.
warnings_justification: cargo fmt is used, and `unsafe` code is forbidden.
warnings_strict_justification: Not yet as strict as possible, there are some clippy lints not fixed.
know_secure_design_justification: I am familiar with those safety principles.
delivery_mitm_justification: Cargo handles fetching and checksumming when the project is used as a dependency.  https or ssh is used when checking out the code from github.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No critical vulnerabilities reported yet, but they will be prioritized if there is any.
static_analysis_justification: On the other hand, the default static conde analysis done by the rust compiler is probably more comprehensive than some such separate tools.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Fussing is only done sporadically, yet.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: The Rust static analysis fails the compiler if there is a problem.  Other than that no such vulnerabilities has been discovered yet, but in case they are, they should be dealt with urgently.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio:
The repo (branches plus pull requests) are built and tested on travis and appveyor.
https://travis-ci.org/kaj/rsass
https://ci.appveyor.com/project/kaj/rsass
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests.
hardened_site_justification: // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff".

test_justification: Test suites are in the [tests folder](https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/tree/tests), with documentation in the [User Guide](https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/blob/docs/User_Guide.md)
test_invocation_justification: A script for invoking the data-loading tests is in [tests folder](https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/tree/tests), with documentation in the [User Guide](https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/blob/docs/User_Guide.md).
test_most_justification: Testing of data consolidation is complete and completely documented. Testing for the analytics is not yet complete. See [tests folder](https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/tree/tests) and [User Guide](https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/blob/docs/User_Guide.md)
tests_are_added_justification: This will be met for the next version.
tests_documented_added_justification: We do not have formal change proposals. Small project with few contributors and one admin.
warnings_fixed_justification: Branches are tested in pycharm before merge.
warnings_strict_justification: There are several warnings built into the loading process, including creation of *.warnings and *.errors files for ease of use.
delivery_mitm_justification: Currently delivery method is limited to download of the open source code from GitHub.
delivery_unsigned_justification: Currently delivery method is limited to download of the open source code from GitHub.
static_analysis_often_justification: This analysis is done regularly, but the project is not worked on daily.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: With so few current contributors to the code itself (as opposed to the munging parameters and jurisdiction data needed to add data from particular files), the core team reviews code personally. Nothing can be merged without admin review. https://github.com/ElectionDataAnalysis/election_data_analysis/pulls
